<h3 id="LawTre">Laws and Treaties</h3>

<ul>

<li>United Nations,

<ul>

<li>1966,
 <a href="https://treaties.un.org/doc/treaties/1976/03/19760323%2006-17%20am/ch_iv_04.pdf" target="other">International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights (ICCPR)</a>.
 Came into force 23 March 1976.</li>

<li>1979,
 <a href="https://www.ohchr.org/en/instruments-mechanisms/instruments/convention-elimination-all-forms-discrimination-against-women" target="other">Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Discrimination Against Women (CEDAW)</a>.
 Came into force 3 September 1981.</li>

<li>1989,
 <a href="https://www.ohchr.org/en/instruments-mechanisms/instruments/convention-rights-child" target="other">Convention on the Rights of the Child (CRC)</a>.
 Came into force 2 September 1990.</li>

<li>1993,
 <a href="https://www.ohchr.org/en/instruments-mechanisms/instruments/declaration-elimination-violence-against-women" target="other">Declaration on the Elimination of Violence Against Women (DEVAW)</a>.
 Ratified 20 December 1993.</li>

<li>2000,
 <a href="https://www.ohchr.org/en/instruments-mechanisms/instruments/protocol-prevent-suppress-and-punish-trafficking-persons" target="other">Protocol to Prevent, Suppress and Punish Trafficking in Persons, Especially Women and Children</a>
 (a Palermo Protocol). Came into force 25 December 2003. Supplements
CEDAW.</li>
</ul> </li>

<li  id="Article21"><a href="https://fra.europa.eu/en/eu-charter/article/21-non-discrimination" target="other">Charter of Fundamental Rights of the European Union, Article 21 - Non-discrimination</a></li>
 
<li id="EU2000">Council of the European Union,
 <a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/PDF/?uri=CELEX:32000L0078" target="other">Council Directive 2000/78/EC of 27 November 2000 establishing a general framework for equal treatment in employment and occupation (pdf)</a></li>
 
<li  id="EU2011"><a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/HTML/?uri=CELEX%3A32011L0093" target="other">Directive 2011/92/EU of the European Parliament and of the Council</a>
 of 13 December 2011 on combating the sexual abuse and sexual
exploitation of children and child pornography, and replacing Council
Framework Decision 2004/68/JHA.</li>

<li id="ukporn">UK, 2024,
 <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/calls-for-evidence/pornography-regulation-legislation-and-enforcement" target="other">Closed call for evidence: Pornography regulation, legislation and enforcement</a></li>
 
<li id="ACA1557">US, 2010,
 <a href="https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/42/18116" target="other">&sect; 1557 of the Affordable Care Act (ACA)</a>,
 42 U.S. Code &sect; 18116 &ndash; Nondiscrimination.</li>

<li  id="IDCode"><a href="https://law.justia.com/codes/idaho/title-18/chapter-88/section-18-8807/" target="other">ID Code &sect; 18-8807 (2023)</a>.
 Idaho Fetal Heartbeat Preborn Child Protection Act: Civil Causes of
Action.</li>
</ul>

